The equation above also assumes that there are no feedbacks that can respond to the change in temperature, so let\'92s add one in. Adding in a feedback means that some part of the temperature response gets added back into the radiative forcing, so it can increase or reduce the initial forcing (increasing the forcing is a positive feedback, reducing the forcing is a negative feedback). The simplest representation of this small radiative addition is linear, \\(c_1 \\Delta T\\), with the parameter \\(c_1\\). So then we have that \
