\
and solving for  \\(\\Delta T\\) we have \
\
\\[\\Delta T = \\frac\{\\lambda \\Delta R\}\{1-c_1\\lambda\} \\; .\\]\
\
This equation is often simplified slightly by introducing the \'91feedback factor\'92 \\(f=c_1\\lambda\\), so that\
\
\\[\\Delta T = \\frac\{\\lambda \\Delta R\}\{1-f\} \\; .\\]\
\
Mathematically, a negative feedback means that \\(f\\) is negative, while a positive feedback means that \\(f\\) is positive. It turns out that if we have several different feedbacks, these can just be added into \\(f\\) (e.g., for three feedbacks \\(f=f_1+f_2+f_3\\)).\
